sub_title: Master of Laws - LLM in International Commercial Law with International Dispute Resolution (Arbitration), University of Reading
summary: I am a recent LLM graduate with legal experience gained through advisory at an independent charity and assistance to court judges. At the moment exploring opportunities to restart my career as a legal/paralegal  and aiming to develop and excel in this area. My recent work and study experience gave me an opportunity to show and improve my communication and organisational skills, ability to multitask and quickly adapt to new environments and challenges, as well as ability to prioritize and work independently. I consider myself a good team player and always strive for continuous learning and professional development.
